activity.title:
Thrilled to see our team's vision for Aurient taking shape through this amazing opportunity! At Aurient, we're not just creating another social media platform; we're embarking on a journey to revolutionize how the world connects, shares, and engages online.

As a co-founder, witnessing our idea evolve from a shared dream into a reality that could change the future of social media is beyond exciting. It's a journey filled with innovation, creativity, and, most importantly, a deep commitment to building something meaningful for our global community.
We're looking for passionate individuals who are ready to challenge the status quo, push boundaries, and join us in this incredible adventure. If you're a Backend Developer, Frontend Developer, Lead Developer, or Designer who shares our vision, your skills could help shape the future of social media.

Let's make history together! Dive into the details of our open positions and become part of a team that values innovation, collaboration, and making a lasting impact. #JoinAurient #socialmedia #techinnovation #wearehiring Join Aurient's Mission to shape the future of Social Media: We're Hiring Backend Developers, Frontend Developers, Lead Developers, and Designers!

At Aurient, we're on a mission to redefine the landscape of social media. Our vision is a platform that's not just innovative but transformative, setting new benchmarks for connectivity, creativity, and community. To turn this vision into reality, we need a team of exceptional talents, individuals who are not just skilled but truly stand out in their fields.

Lead developer:

Main: 
Proficient in either Python - (Django), JavaScript - Express.js or other relevant frameworks. 
Proficient in React Native or Swift.
Created/Worked with relevant projects within mobile app creation
Familiarity with Git
Familiarity with leading team projects. 
Ability to create sustainable and saleable framework architectures
Ability to mentor junior developers and managing deadlines and work hours
Experience with either Notion or Jira, or other relevant project management tools

We like to see:
Experienced working with full-stack development 
Experience working as a lead developer
Higher-level Education in software engineering or computer science
Projects, projects, projects!
Planning and coordination skills.

Backend Developers:

Main: 
Proficient in Python, JavaScript
Proficient in relevant low-level language (C, C#, Java, etc.)
Proficient working with databases, such as MySQL or other relevant languages
Proficient working with Google Cloud
Proficient working with REST APIs 

We like to see: 
Experience working as a backend developer
Higher-level Education in software engineering or computer science
Projects, projects, projects!
Planning and coordination skills
Innovation Mindset and a passion for new technologies

Frontend Developers:

Main:
Experience working as a frontend developer 
Familiar frameworks such as Django, Express.js, React
Proficient in Swift or React Native 
Proficient in HTML, CSS and JavaScript 
Able to create projects that work on both mobile, tablet and desktop

We like to see:
Experience working as a frontend developer
Higher-level Education in software engineering or computer science
Projects, projects, projects!
Planning and coordination skills
Visual Creativity, show us your artistic designs and projects!

Designers:

Main:
Proficient in Figma
2+ years working with app development
Background in user interface design principles and user testing

We like to see:
Higher-level education in design or relevant fields
Planning and coordination skills

If you are excited about our project, do not hesitate to contact us! We are open for discussions and you might be the right candidate! 

Let's change the future of social media, together. contact@aurient.co
Congrats Saad!

activity.title: I'm excited to share that I've started my internship at Stax Capital as a Trader & Business Analyst Intern, and I'm thrilled to be part of the Data Science team. Last Thursday, my business partner and I had the privilege of pitching our startup idea. We're incredibly thankful for the opportunity to share our vision and receive thoughtful feedback from such insightful mentors. Being part of BI Startup means we can continuously refine our project, and I'm excited to see where this journey takes us.

Turns out that there is an I in teAIm! Because for Globeducate schools, safe and effective AI integration is a collective journey. In my work, I‚Äôve witnessed first-hand how essential collaboration is in this endeavour. Our success hinges on every member of our education community safely using AI driven tools; contributing, learning, and adapting.

I was so lucky to catch up with a part of our power teAIm who represents leadership in British International education in Spain - as we gathered at the National Association of British Schools in Spain (NABSS) 46th conference in Valencia, Spain this weekend. 

A big thank you to Professor Mick Waters - one of our esteemed members of the Globeducate Global Advisory Board - for his enlightening key note: ‚ÄúThe leadership imperative: Making learning matter‚Äù. As he, rightfully, pointed out, we have pushed technology into schools for decades, but it never really changed how we educate. The new AI technologies will bring in those changes and we have to work together on developing our pedagogy. Thank you Mick! It was great to see you again. 

I must extend my sincere gratitude to Oahn Crouch Daniel Jones , Adam Hassoun , Harry Ainscough  Dominic Abbott, Suzannah and Chris Long for their unwavering commitment and innovative thinking. You constantly impress me, I am so delighted to work with you, and your contributions and leadership are invaluable as we navigate the future of AI in education together.

Looking ahead, I am excited about my visit to Cambridge House British International School on Monday. It presents a fantastic opportunity to work closely with parents, pupils, teachers, and the leadership team on furthering our partnership in AI integration and the safe use of technology. These dialogues are critical for shaping an educational environment that is not only technologically advanced but also secure and nurturing for our students.

Moreover, I want to congratulate Cambridge House on the remarkable achievements at the Cambridge International Education awards ceremony. I have had an amazing opportunity to be a student visitor at Bett Global , a major conference concerning AI implementation and distribution in educational institutions and developments. 

As a University of Nottingham student, it is extremely insightful to attend such ever evolving space that fully emerges you in the world of AI and tech. This allows you to see all the different ways how you can immerse your experience as a student with modern digital technologies!

The importance of growing AI influence in the world of education is an interesting journey for a student, and it is quite hard to navigate yourself through all new AI technologie and find the ones you can trust. 

I want to say HUGE thank you to my mentor Clara Lin Hawking who encouraged me to attend this event with her.
